  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba3 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 600 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vomiting for 600 people in matrimonial homes",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The health department of the Gangavathakorala local council has started detailed investigations regarding the incident where around 600 people who had attended several wedding events in one of the main hotels in the Ambitiya area suddenly fell ill.",
        "A few days ago three wedding ceremonies were held in the hotel and around six hundred people who attended the three wedding ceremonies suffered from vomiting, diarrhea and fever and had to be treated in private and government hospitals.",
        "The wedding ceremony of a family member of a famous businessman from Kandy was also held at the said hotel and it is reported that the married couple had to be admitted to the hospital while they had gone abroad for their honeymoon.",
        "When a senior official of the Gangavathakorala Local Government Council was asked about this, the hotel water samples were sent to the University of Peradeniya for further tests as it is suspected that the people who ate at the hotel may have developed an allergy to the hotel water.",
        "He also said that there has been a problem in conducting the investigations as complaints have been received about the incident a few days after the incident."
      ],
